CNCP v1 23118
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11730: When the variable in a v-for loop has the same name as the component being rendered, the element may not render in the production build.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:17.905848+00:00",
  "text": "When the variable in a v-for loop has the same name as the component being rendered, the element may not render in the production build.\n\n### Vue version\n\n @42e8df6\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClick the ‘dev’ button to switch to prod causes the Comp component not to render. \n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe dev and prod environments are consistent || Dev throw a warning\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nWhy is there a difference between the dev and prod environments?\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: sfc",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
